{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775863759290,"sessionID":"ses_28645eb9cffeDEBJBa63mnSzqs","part":{"id":"prt_d79ba7d0f001sl6w4lj1D778d4","messageID":"msg_d79ba702c00149fO7BCJj622Gx","sessionID":"ses_28645eb9cffeDEBJBa63mnSzqs","type":"tool","tool":"bash","callID":"toolu_ca6e614cd08b45cfa601606e","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"command":"mkdir -p /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-023","description":"Create AR-023 directory"},"output":"","metadata":{"output":"","exit":0,"description":"Create AR-023 directory","truncated":false},"title":"Create AR-023 directory","time":{"start":1775863759211,"end":1775863759288}}}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775863759318,"sessionID":"ses_28645eb9cffeDEBJBa63mnSzqs","part":{"id":"prt_d79ba81ba001XWbfss36jff2yI","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d79ba702c00149fO7BCJj622Gx","sessionID":"ses_28645eb9cffeDEBJBa63mnSzqs","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":39179,"input":3830,"output":151,"reasoning":0,"cache":{"write":0,"read":35198}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775863760950,"sessionID":"ses_28645eb9cffeDEBJBa63mnSzqs","part":{"id":"prt_d79ba8834001JgCh1948qTNBKv","messageID":"msg_d79ba81ed0017w6sh34azkz7u3","sessionID":"ses_28645eb9cffeDEBJBa63mnSzqs","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775863818926,"sessionID":"ses_28645eb9cffeDEBJBa63mnSzqs","part":{"id":"prt_d79ba8ab7001eH3D50MDRPWJfq","messageID":"msg_d79ba81ed0017w6sh34azkz7u3","sessionID":"ses_28645eb9cffeDEBJBa63mnSzqs","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_c17b9f8860f747a186ff2e7f","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# Delta Spec: AR-023 — CLI invoke/status 命令\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing the CLI invoke and status commands in the AgentCube CLI tool (`kubectl-agentcube`).\n\n## Base Specifications\n\n- **AR**: AR-023\n- **Module**: `cmd/cli`\n- **Language**: Python\n- **Size**: M\n\n---\n\n## Background\n\nThe `invoke` command sends JSON payloads to deployed agents via the AgentCube Router or standard Kubernetes Service. The `status` command retrieves and displays the current status of deployed agents. Both commands work with either the AgentCube provider (AgentRuntime CR) or the standard Kubernetes provider (Deployment + Service).\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### AR-023-001: invoke CLI interface\n\nThe system SHALL expose the `invoke` command via Typer with specific options.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-023-001-A — Invoke command options\n\n- **GIVEN** the user runs `kubectl-agentcube invoke --help`\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL display:\n  - `-f, --workspace PATH` — Path to agent workspace (default: \".\")\n  - `--payload JSON` — JSON-formatted input passed to the agent (default: \"{}\")\n  - `--header KEY:VALUE` — Custom HTTP headers (repeatable)\n  - `--provider PROVIDER` — Target provider: 'agentcube' or 'k8s' (default: \"agentcube\")\n  - `--verbose` — Enable detailed logging\n\n#### Scenario: AR-023-001-B — Default options\n\n- **GIVEN** the user runs `invoke` with no options\n- **THEN** defaults SHALL be applied:\n  - `workspace`: `\".\"`\n  - `payload`: `\"{}\"`\n  - `header_list`: `None`\n  - `provider`: `\"agentcube\"`\n  - `verbose`: `False`\n\n---\n\n### AR-023-002: invoke payload parsing\n\nThe system SHALL parse and validate the JSON payload.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-023-002-A — Valid JSON payload\n\n- **GIVEN** `--payload` contains valid JSON (e.g., `{\"message\": \"hello\"}`)\n- **WHEN** the command parses it\n- **THEN** the system SHALL convert it to a Python dict for the HTTP request body\n\n#### Scenario: AR-023-002-B — Invalid JSON payload\n\n- **GIVEN** `--payload` contains invalid JSON (e.g., `{invalid}`)\n- **WHEN** the command parses it\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL print \"Invalid JSON payload: {parse_error}\" in red\n- **AND** exit with code `1` before calling `_handle_error`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-023-002-C — Empty payload default\n\n- **GIVEN** the user runs `invoke` without `--payload`\n- **WHEN** the command parses the default `\"{}\"`\n- **THEN** the system SHALL use an empty dict `{}` as the request body\n\n---\n\n### AR-023-003: invoke header parsing\n\nThe system SHALL parse custom HTTP headers from the command line.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-023-003-A — Valid headers\n\n- **GIVEN** `--header \"Authorization: Bearer token\"` is provided\n- **WHEN** headers are parsed\n- **THEN** the system SHALL add `{\"Authorization\": \"Bearer token\"}` to the request headers\n\n#### Scenario: AR-023-003-B — Multiple headers\n\n- **GIVEN** multiple `--header` options are provided\n- **WHEN** headers are parsed\n- **THEN** all headers SHALL be merged into the request\n\n#### Scenario: AR-023-003-C — Invalid header format\n\n- **GIVEN** a header string without a single `:` separator (e.g., `InvalidHeader`)\n- **WHEN** headers are parsed\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL print \"Invalid header format: '{header}'. Expected key:value\" in red\n- **AND** exit with code `1`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-023-003-D — Header with multiple colons\n\n- **GIVEN** a header string with multiple colons (e.g., `Authorization: Bearer:token`)\n- **WHEN** headers are parsed\n- **THEN** the system SHALL split on the first colon only, resulting in `{\"Authorization\": \"Bearer:token\"}`\n\n---\n\n### AR-023-004: invoke prerequisites\n\nThe system SHALL validate invoke prerequisites before making requests.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-023-004-A — Validate workspace exists\n\n- **GIVEN** the specified workspace path does not exist\n- **WHEN** invoke runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `FileNotFoundError`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-023-004-B — Validate metadata exists\n\n- **GIVEN** the workspace does not contain `agent_metadata.yaml`\n- **WHEN** invoke runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `FileNotFoundError`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-023-004-C — Validate agent is published\n\n- **GIVEN** metadata has no `agent_id` (not published)\n- **WHEN** invoke runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL print \"Agent has not been published. Run 'kubectl-agentcube publish' first.\" in yellow\n- **AND** exit with code `1`\n\n---\n\n### AR-023-005: invoke agentcube provider\n\nThe system SHALL invoke agents via the AgentCube Router when provider is \"agentcube\".\n\n#### Scenario: AR-023-005-A — Get endpoint from metadata\n\n- **GIVEN** provider is \"agentcube\" and metadata contains `agent_endpoint`\n- **WHEN** `_validate_invoke_prerequisites` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return the endpoint URL, namespace, and agent name\n\n#### Scenario: AR-023-005-B — Session header from metadata\n\n- **GIVEN** metadata contains `session_id`\n- **WHEN** `InvokeRuntime.invoke` runs\n- **THEN** the HTTP client SHALL add header `X-Agentcube-Session-Id` with the session_id value\n\n#### Scenario: AR-023-005-C — URL rewrite for AgentRuntime\n\n- **GIVEN** `k8s_deployment.type == \"AgentRuntime\"` in metadata\n- **WHEN** invoking the agent\n- **THEN** the system SHALL rewrite the URL to `{base}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-023-005-D — Missing router_url\n\n- **GIVEN** provider is \"agentcube\" but metadata lacks `router_url`\n- **WHEN** invoke runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` with message about missing router_url\n\n---\n\n### AR-023-006: invoke k8s provider\n\nThe system SHALL invoke agents via Kubernetes Service when provider is \"k8s\".\n\n#### Scenario: AR-023-006-A — Get service URL from metadata\n\n- **GIVEN** provider is \"k8s\" and metadata contains `k8s_deployment.service_url`\n- **WHEN** invoke runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL use that URL as the invocation endpoint\n\n#### Scenario: AR-023-006-B — Missing service URL\n\n- **GIVEN** provider is \"k8s\" but metadata lacks `k8s_deployment.service_url`\n- **WHEN** invoke runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` with message about missing service_url\n\n---\n\n### AR-023-007: invoke HTTP request\n\nThe system SHALL send HTTP requests to the agent endpoint.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-023-007-A — POST request with JSON body\n\n- **GIVEN** a valid endpoint and payload\n- **WHEN** the HTTP request is sent\n- **THEN** the system SHALL POST with `Content-Type: application/json` and body as JSON\n\n#### Scenario: AR-023-007-B — Response handling\n\n- **GIVEN** the agent returns a successful response\n- **WHEN** invoke completes\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL print the response body (formatted if JSON)\n\n#### Scenario: AR-023-007-C — HTTP error handling\n\n- **GIVEN** the agent returns an HTTP error (4xx/5xx)\n- **WHEN** invoke processes the response\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL print the error in red with status code\n- **AND** exit with code `1`\n\n---\n\n### AR-023-008: status CLI interface\n\nThe system SHALL expose the `status` command via Typer with specific options.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-023-008-A — Status command options\n\n- **GIVEN** the user runs `kubectl-agentcube status --help`\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL display:\n  - `-f, --workspace PATH` — Path to agent workspace (default: \".\")\n  - `--provider PROVIDER` — Target provider: 'agentcube' or 'k8s' (default: \"agentcube\")\n  - `--verbose` — Enable detailed logging\n\n#### Scenario: AR-023-008-B — Default options\n\n- **GIVEN** the user runs `status` with no options\n- **THEN** defaults SHALL be applied:\n  - `workspace`: `\".\"`\n  - `provider`: `\"agentcube\"`\n  - `verbose`: `False`\n\n---\n\n### AR-023-009: status prerequisites\n\nThe system SHALL validate status prerequisites before querying.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-023-009-A — Validate workspace exists\n\n- **GIVEN** the specified workspace path does not exist\n- **WHEN** status runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `FileNotFoundError`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-023-009-B — Validate metadata exists\n\n- **GIVEN** the workspace does not contain `agent_metadata.yaml`\n- **WHEN** status runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `FileNotFoundError`\n\n---\n\n### AR-023-010: status not published\n\nThe system SHALL handle the case where the agent has not been published.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-023-010-A — Not published status\n\n- **GIVEN** metadata has no `agent_id`\n- **WHEN** `get_status` returns `status == \"not_published\"`\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL print \"Agent has not been published. Run 'kubectl-agentcube publish' first.\" in yellow\n- **AND** exit with code `1`\n\n---\n\n### AR-023-011: status agentcube provider\n\nThe system SHALL retrieve AgentRuntime CR status when provider is \"agentcube\".\n\n#### Scenario: AR-023-011-A — CR exists with status\n\n- **GIVEN** provider is \"agentcube\" and the AgentRuntime CR exists with status\n- **WHEN** `_get_cr_k8s_status` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL read `cr_object[\"status\"]` for `status` and `agentEndpoint`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-023-011-B — CR exists without status\n\n- **GIVEN** provider is \"agentcube\" and the AgentRuntime CR exists but has no status field\n- **WHEN** `_get_cr_k8s_status` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return status as \"created_no_status\"\n\n#### Scenario: AR-023-011-C — CR not found\n\n- **GIVEN** provider is \"agentcube\" and the AgentRuntime CR does not exist\n- **WHEN** `_get_cr_k8s_status` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return status as \"not_found_in_k8s\"\n\n---\n\n### AR-023-012: status k8s provider\n\nThe system SHALL retrieve Kubernetes Deployment status when provider is \"k8s\".\n\n#### Scenario: AR-023-012-A — Deployment status\n\n- **GIVEN** provider is \"k8s\" and the Deployment exists\n- **WHEN** `_get_k8s_status` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return deployment status including:\n  - Available replicas\n  - Ready replicas\n  - Namespace\n\n#### Scenario: AR-023-012-B — Deployment not found\n\n- **GIVEN** provider is \"k8s\" and the Deployment does not exist\n- **WHEN** `_get_k8s_status` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return status as \"not_found\"\n\n---\n\n### AR-023-013: status output display\n\nThe system SHALL display status information using Rich formatting.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-023-013-A — Status table display\n\n- **GIVEN** status is retrieved successfully\n- **WHEN** the command displays results\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL use a Rich `Table` with columns:\n  - Field\n  - Value\n- **AND** display: Agent Name, Provider, Status, Endpoint/Service URL\n\n#### Scenario: AR-023-013-B — Status error exit\n\n- **GIVEN** status is `\"not_published\"` or `\"error\"`\n- **WHEN** the command runs\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL exit with code `1`\n\n---\n\n### AR-023-014: Error handling\n\nThe system SHALL handle errors with appropriate error messages and exit codes.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-023-014-A — Invoke error with verbose logging\n\n- **GIVEN** invoke raises an exception\n- **WHEN** `--verbose` flag is enabled\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL print error message in red with full traceback\n- **AND** exit with code `1`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-023-014-B — Status error with verbose logging\n\n- **GIVEN** status raises an exception\n- **WHEN** `--verbose` flag is enabled\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL print error message in red with full traceback\n- **AND** exit with code `1`\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] AC001: Invoke command accepts all specified CLI options (workspace, payload, header, provider, verbose)\n- [ ] AC002: Invoke validates JSON payload and exits with code 1 for invalid JSON\n- [ ] AC003: Invoke validates header format and exits with code 1 for invalid headers\n- [ ] AC004: Invoke adds session header (X-Agentcube-Session-Id) when session_id exists in metadata\n- [ ] AC005: Invoke validates agent is published before attempting to invoke\n- [ ] AC006: Invoke rewrites URL for AgentRuntime CR deployments\n- [ ] AC007: Invoke sends POST request with JSON body and appropriate headers\n- [ ] AC008: Status command accepts all specified CLI options (workspace, provider, verbose)\n- [ ] AC009: Status validates workspace and metadata exist before proceeding\n- [ ] AC010: Status returns \"not_published\" and exits with code 1 when agent not published\n- [ ] AC011: Status retrieves AgentRuntime CR status for agentcube provider\n- [ ] AC012: Status retrieves Deployment status for k8s provider\n- [ ] AC013: Status displays results in Rich Table format\n- [ ] AC014: Both commands handle errors with appropriate exit codes and verbose logging\n\n---\n\n## Architecture Notes\n\n### Key Components\n\n| Component | Path | Description |\n|-----------|------|-------------|\n| CLI Entry | `agentcube/cli/main.py` | Typer app with `invoke` and `status` commands |\n| InvokeRuntime | `agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py` | Core invoke logic |\n| StatusRuntime | `agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py` | Core status logic |\n| MetadataService | `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` | Metadata CRUD operations |\n| AgentMetadata | `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` | Metadata model with validators |\n\n### Invoke Flow\n\n```\ninvoke command (provider=agentcube)\n    └─> InvokeRuntime.invoke()\n            ├─> _validate_invoke_prerequisites()\n            │       └─> Returns: endpoint, namespace, agent_name\n            └─> _invoke_agent_via_agentcube()\n                    └─> POST to router with session header\n\ninvoke command (provider=k8s)\n    └─> InvokeRuntime.invoke()\n            └─> _direct_http_invocation()\n                    └─> POST to k8s service URL\n```\n\n### Status Flow\n\n```\nstatus command (provider=agentcube)\n    └─> StatusRuntime.get_status()\n            └─> _get_cr_k8s_status()\n                    └─> Query AgentRuntime CR\n\nstatus command (provider=k8s)\n    └─> StatusRuntime.get_status()\n            └─> _get_k8s_status()\n                    └─> Query Deployment/Service\n```\n\n### CLI Options Mapping\n\n| Command | CLI Option | Runtime Parameter | Type |\n|---------|------------|-------------------|------|\n| invoke | `-f, --workspace` | workspace_path | str |\n| invoke | `--payload` | payload | str (JSON) |\n| invoke | `--header` | header_list | Optional[List[str]] |\n| invoke | `--provider` | provider | str (default: \"agentcube\") |\n| invoke | `--verbose` | verbose | bool |\n| status | `-f, --workspace` | workspace_path | str |\n| status | `--provider` | provider | str (default: \"agentcube\") |\n| status | `--verbose` | verbose | bool |\n\n### Provider Types\n\n| Provider | Invocation Target | Status Target |\n|----------|-------------------|---------------|\n| `agentcube` | AgentRuntime CR via Router | AgentRuntime CR |\n| `k8s` | Kubernetes Service | Kubernetes Deployment |\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- Base design: `cli-toolkit/design.md`\n- Base spec: `cli-toolkit/spec.md`\n- CLI entry point: `agentcube/cli/main.py`\n- InvokeRuntime implementation: `agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py`\n- StatusRuntime implementation: `agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py`\n- Metadata model: `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`\n- AgentMetadata: `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`\n- Related: AR-022 (publish command)","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-023/delta-spec.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-023/delta-spec.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-023/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775863818914,"end":1775863818923}}}}
